# Cline Workspace Rules

## Scope
These rules apply to all tasks in this workspace.

## Mandatory Workflow
1. Read agent-wiki/README.md before planning or editing.
2. Read relevant wiki subpages for the area you are changing.
3. Perform requested work.
4. Update wiki pages after every change (code, structure, behavior, decisions).
5. Add a concise entry in agent-wiki/changelog.md.

If wiki info is missing, add it before finishing.

## File Structure and Size
- Maximum file length: 200 lines.
- If a file would exceed 200 lines, split it into smaller modules.
- Keep one primary responsibility per file.
- Keep components and logic in separate files.

## Component and Logic Separation
- Presentation components: rendering and event wiring only.
- Logic modules: calculations, state transitions, data transforms.
- Avoid embedding heavy business logic directly in JSX components.
- Reuse logic via hooks, services, or utils.

## Editing Standards
- Make minimal, targeted changes.
- Preserve behavior unless explicitly asked to change it.
- Keep naming consistent with existing project conventions.
- Prefer small, composable functions.

## Wiki Standards
- Agent wiki is the source of truth for architecture and decisions.
- Required wiki updates after changes:
  - agent-wiki/components.md for new or changed components.
  - agent-wiki/architecture.md for structural changes.
  - agent-wiki/decisions.md for non-trivial tradeoffs.
  - agent-wiki/changelog.md for every completed task.
- Keep entries concise and factual.
- Include what changed, why, and impact.

## Completion Checklist
- Confirm all edited files are 200 lines or fewer.
- Confirm component and logic separation is respected.
- Confirm wiki pages are updated.
- Confirm changelog entry exists.
